RE: City Records Request of April 22, 2025, Reference # N000380-042225 Dear Robbie Powelson, The City of Novato received a public records request from you on April 22, 2025. Your request asked for: All communications between Kate Gauntlett and Heather Abrams between January 1st 2025 to April 22nd 2025 

All communications between Lt. Alan Bates and Officer Thomas Lyons between January 1st 2025 to April 22nd 2025 

All communications between Lt. Alan Bates and Capt. Jim Correa and Jim Naugle between January 1st 2025 to April 22nd 2025 Your request as currently stated will likely return thousands of records that will take significant time to collect, examine, and determine disclosability. A more narrowed request will assist the City in providing the requested records promptly. Could you please clarify (1) the types of records you are asking for, and (2) if you would be willing to narrow the date range? Please respond to this email with the details requested above. Upon receipt of clarification, the City of Novato will further respond to your public records request as required by law. For questions or additional information, please reply to this email. Sincerely, Laura McDowall 
City Clerk

communications.subject: City Records Request :: N000380-042225
communications.communication:
--- Please respond above this line --- 
RE: City Records Request of April 22, 2025, Reference # N000380-042225 Dear Robbie Powelson, The City of Novato received a public records request from you on April 22, 2025. Your request asked for: All communications between Kate Gauntlett and Heather Abrams between January 1st 2025 to April 22nd 2025 

All communications between Lt. Alan Bates and Officer Thomas Lyons between January 1st 2025 to April 22nd 2025 

All communications between Lt. Alan Bates and Capt. Jim Correa and Jim Naugle between January 1st 2025 to April 22nd 2025 
The City has determined that it is in possession of records that are responsive to your request.  The final review and distribution of responsive, non-exempt records will be completed in approximately 30 days from the date of this letter. 

By furnishing you this initial response, the City does not waive any of its rights to claim or invoke any exemptions or other grounds for withholding any records located during its research and review which it determines to be responsive to any request but not required to be disclosed under the California Public Records Act. The City intends to provide its grounds for withholding any records at the completion of the review and disclosure process. For questions or additional information, please reply to this email. Sincerely, Laura McDowall 
City Clerk

communications.subject: City Records Request :: N000380-042225
communications.communication:
--- Please respond above this line --- 
RE: City Records Request of April 22, 2025, Reference # N000380-042225 Dear Robbie Powelson, This is in response to your public records request received on April 22, 2025 and follows my message of May 1, 2025.. Your request asked for: All communications between Kate Gauntlett and Heather Abrams between January 1st 2025 to April 22nd 2025 

All communications between Lt. Alan Bates and Officer Thomas Lyons between January 1st 2025 to April 22nd 2025 

All communications between Lt. Alan Bates and Capt. Jim Correa and Jim Naugle between January 1st 2025 to April 22nd 2025 
The City has completed a reasonable search of its records and determined there are responsive documents as well as certain records and/or portions thereof which have been determined to be exempt from disclosure and will therefore not be disclosed pursuant to the statutory exemptions noted below: • Deliberative Process Privilege – Government Code section 7922.000; Times Mirror Co. v. Superior Court (1991) 53 Cal.3d 1325; California First Amendment Coalition v. Superior Court (1998) 67 Cal.App.4th 159 – The public interest in nondisclosure clearly outweighs the public interest in disclosure of records revealing the deliberations of agency officials used to reach a decision. 
• Preliminary Drafts and Similar Materials – Government Code section 7927.500 – Any preliminary drafts, notes, or interagency or intra-agency memoranda that are not retained by a public agency in the ordinary course of business are exempt from disclosure. 
• Personally Identifying Information – Government Code section 7922.000; American Civil Liberties Union Foundation v. Superior Court (2017) 221 Cal.Rptr.3d 832 – The public interest in nondisclosure clearly outweighs the public interest in disclosure of information that infringes upon privacy rights. 

• Official Information Privilege – Government Code section 7927.705, Evidence Code sections 1040 – Information acquired in confidence by a public employee in the course of his or her duty and not open, or officially disclosed, to the public prior to the time the claim of privilege is made. 

• Records Related to Law Enforcement or Security – Government Code section 7923.600 – Records of complaints to, or investigations conducted by, or records of intelligence information or security procedures of … any state or local police agency, or any investigatory or security files compiled by any other state or local police agency, or any investigatory or security files compiled by any other state or local agency for correctional, law enforcement, or licensing purposes. 

• Public interest balancing test - Government Code section 7922.000 – The public interest in nondisclosure clearly outweighs the public interest in disclosure. 
Please log in to the Public Records Center at the following link to retrieve the responsive records: City Records Request - N000380-042225  Please be advised the City will not allow inspection or copying of any privileged documents. While we will try to remove all privileged documents, the inadvertent inclusion of any privileged documents does not constitute a waiver and we ask you to notify us of any privileged material that is inadvertently provided. Also be advised the City is not required to produce documents that are exempt from disclosure under the California Public Records Act, records destroyed in accordance with Government Code section 34090 and the City’s records retention policy, or records that include such information that the public interest served by not disclosing the records clearly outweighs the public interest served by the disclosure of the records. 

Under Government Code section 7922.600, please let me know if you would like to discuss your request further or if I can assist you in clarifying the request, identifying records responsive to the request, or requesting additional records. 
Kindest regards, Laura McDowall 
City Clerk

title: Request for Correctional Mental Health Staff Directory and Contact Information (Department of Corrections)

communications.subject: Iowa Open Records Law Request: Request for Correctional Mental Health Staff Directory and Contact Information (Department of Corrections)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Iowa Open Records Law, I hereby request the following records:

I am requesting a list of currently employed mental health professionals within your state's Department of Corrections or its subsidiary agencies, as well as their contact information.

Specifically, I am requesting:

- Full names
- Job titles
- Assigned correctional facility
- Government-issued email addresses
- Government-issued phone numbers (direct desk numbers if available, otherwise department phone numbers with or without extensions)
- Department/division (e.g. Behavioral Health, Mental Health Services)

This request applies to the following roles: rehabilitative program coordinators, licensed psychologists, psychiatrists, clinical social workers, and other licensed mental health professionals serving incarcerated populations in state-operated facilities.

If available, I request this information be provided in a machine-readable format such as CSV or Excel.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Andrew Ma

communications.communication:

Thank you for your response and for providing the fee estimate for Request 25-1850.

I’d like to respectfully amend the scope of the request, as our organization is a small nonprofit working to offer free, trauma-informed mindfulness and meditation programs to support the mental health of incarcerated individuals. Unfortunately, we do not currently have funding to cover the cost of the full record request.

Instead, I’d be very grateful if you could provide the name, title, work email, and phone number of  supervisory-level staff at the Iowa Department of Corrections who are responsible for overseeing or coordinating mental health services or programming within state correctional facilities.

I understand this may fall outside of a formal records search and hope this more limited request is feasible without significant cost. Any partial guidance or contact information you’re able to share would be sincerely appreciated.

Thank you again for your time and support.

Warm regards,
Andrew Ma

communications.subject: Massachusetts Public Records Law Request: Affirmatively Forwarding Fair Housing
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Massachusetts Public Records Law, I hereby request the following records:

Mayor Michelle Wu signed, on January 20, 2022, “An Executive Order Relative to Affirmatively Furthering Fair Housing and the Implementation of the City of Boston’s Assessment of Fair Housing.” https://www.boston.gov/sites/default/files/file/2022/01/220120%20AFH%20Executive%20Order.pdf

A Squares and Streets initiative was started by the Boston Planning Department on or around January 2024 https://www.bostonplans.org/planning-zoning/planning-initiatives/squares-streets

We request all documents dated from January 1, 2021 to the present about the “Executive Order…Assessment of Fair Housing” and the Boston Squares and Streets initiative 
Documents should include, but are not limited to, reports, minutes, meeting notes, conversation notes, office notes, and emails. Specifically, please include communications between members of the Affirmatively Further Fair Housing (AFFH) Community Advisory Committee (CAC) and the Boston Planning Department. This would include but not be limited to James Jemison, Aimee Chambers, Abdul-Razak Zachariah, Mohammed Missouri, Devin Quirk, Kathleen Onufer, Caitlin Coppinger, Ruthzee Louijeune, Enrique Pepen, Margaret F. Turner, Eileen Michaud, Nadine Cohen, Amelia Najjar, Tim Davis, James Jennings, William Onuoha, Sheila Dillon and Kairos Shen.

I also request that, if appropriate, fees be waived as we believe this request is in the public interest, as suggested but not stipulated by the recommendations of the Massachusetts Supervisor of Public Records. The requested documents will be made available to the general public free of charge as part of the public information service at MuckRock.com, and is not made for commercial usage.

I expect the request to be filled in an accessible format, including for screen readers, which provide text-to-speech for persons unable to read print. Files that are not accessible to screen readers include, for example, .pdf image files as well as physical documents.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Alice Bonner

communications.subject: Re: Massachusetts Public Records Law Request: Affirmatively Forwarding Fair Housing
communications.communication:
Good morning Alice,

Thank you for your help - I will let you know if I have any other questions
for you as I run these searches. Due to the broad nature of your request
and the volume of records that will need to be sorted through, I expect we
will be able to produce the records within 25 business days of the original
receipt of your request.

One quick note as your request includes communications with other City
staff and Council members — I’m only able to search records that are within
the custody and control of the Planning Department and the BPDA so any
emails that don’t include someone from Planning or BPDA would fall outside
the scope of what I can access. For example, if there’s an email between
someone in the Mayor’s Office and a community advocate that doesn’t copy a
Planning or BPDA staff member, it wouldn’t appear in my search. Those c
ommunications are maintained by the City’s Public Records Office, which
coordinates records requests across other City departments.

You can submit a public records request to the City’s Public Records Office
via the following link:



Boston City Public Records Center
<https://bostonma.govqa.us/WEBAPP/_rs/(S(jn2bhvbuesn4eumcufollldk))/supporthome.aspx>
Best,
Danielle

communications.subject: RE: Massachusetts Public Records Law Request: Affirmatively Forwarding Fair Housing
communications.communication:
Subject: Follow-up on Records Request

Good morning Danielle,

Thank you for your helpful note.

I understand that the searches may return a large volume of records and that additional time may be needed for review. That is completely understandable. I would appreciate it if you could share documents with me as they are identified and reviewed.

In particular, if possible, could you please retrieve these materials first? Being emails and documents sent to the Planning Department between January 15, 2024, and February 15, 2024. These would be addressed to leadership in the Planning Department—Chief James Jemison, Director Aimee Chambers, and Director Abdul-Razak Zachariah—from Margaret Turner of Greater Boston Legal Services. It’s possible that members of the City of Boston Affirmatively Furthering Fair Housing Community Advisory Committee were included on some or all of this correspondence.

Thank you also for your recommendation regarding records that do not include staff from the BPDA or Planning Department. I appreciate your suggestion to follow up with the City’s Public Records Office for those materials.

Best regards,
Alice

communications.subject: New York Freedom of Information Law Request: Evergreen Solutions (Niagara County Community College)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law, I hereby request the following records:

To Whom It May Concern:


Subject: Request for Public Records - 

Greetings,

I hope this email finds you well. We at Evergreen Solutions, LLC, are conducting a compensation study on behalf of our client and I am writing to make a formal open records request. We are requesting an electronic copy of your staff and faculty (if applicable) database as well as relevant documents such as job descriptions, collective bargaining agreements, and pay plans. I am able to send survey templates to assist with the data collection; however, we will accept data in the manner most convenient for you.

Staff Census Information requested:

Job Titles
Classification Title
Pay Grades
Pay Ranges (Minimum and Maximum)
Actual Salaries
Full-Time Equivalent (FTE) Status
Staff Handbook

I also kindly request answers to the following questions related to the compensation study:

How are salaries adjusted for your organization (e.g., COLA, Longevity, performance, etc.)?
What is your current turnover rate?
What is your current average tenure for an employee?
Date your current compensation plan was implemented.
Date of the last salary adjustment?
How frequently are job descriptions updated?

For the faculty database, I am requesting the following information:

Faculty Census:
Rank (if applicable)
Classification Title (if faculty holds other positions other than teaching such as Dean, Chair, Coordinators,etc)
Highest Degree Held
Pay Grade
Pay Ranges (Min& Max)
Current Step (if on a step plan)
Contract Length (in days and/or months)
Annual Base Salary with no additives
Annual Salary with any additives
Discipline (Not to be confused with department, the distinct/specific subject the faculty member teaches; Ex: Microbiology)
Department
CIP Code (if available - by individual incumbent)

Additionally, copies of the following documents, if available:

Copy of all faculty pay plans
Employee Benefit Information (Holidays Off, Health Insurance, Etc)
Salary Adjustment Policy (Longevity, performance, COLA, etc)
Any Collective Bargaining Agreements
Current Turnover Rate
Current Average Tenure
Date that your current pay plan was implemented
Date of your last salary adjustment to pay plan
How frequently are your job descriptions updated
Do you have a planned salary adjustment to your compensation structures for the next fiscal year? If so, by what amount?
Please list/attach and supplements/additives that faculty are compensated for duties outside of instruction
Faculty Handbooks
Adjunct Rates/Pay Plan
Overload Rates
Rates for compensation for faculty leadership- Deans, Coordinators, Department Chairs
Do you compensate faculty differently based on area of discipline? If yes, please provide details.
Do you have any form of additional compensation for Large Class Size? If yes, please provide details.
Do you have an education incentive at your institution? If yes, please provide details.

I understand that public records requests may involve administrative processes and associated fees, as allowed by law. Please inform me of any fees and the estimated timeframe for fulfilling this request. If any portion of this request is denied, please provide a written explanation for the denial, citing the specific legal grounds for the refusal.

Please consider this email as a formal request for public records under the applicable open records laws. If there are any questions or additional details needed to process this request, please do not hesitate to contact me.

I look forward to your prompt attention to this matter and the timely provision of the requested information. Your cooperation in ensuring transparency and access to public records is greatly appreciated.

Do you agree to the redaction of information that is subject to mandatory exceptions, provided such redactions are clearly labeled on information you receive?: Yes
Do you agree to the redaction of information that is subject to discretionary exceptions, provided such redactions are clearly labeled on information you receive? Yes

Email: alisia@consultevergreen.com

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Alisia Rios

I have the answers to your questions. 

1. Is the salary structure reflective of all the employees? Meaning these are all the employees who work at the institution? Wanted to ask since there were only 48 positions.

Answer: The information provided was for Administrators. All other employees are in a CBA. 

- Is there anything to indicate the actual salary and their FTE? 

Answer: That is the actual salary as FTE. 

2. Are these "groups" official pay grades for the employees?

Answer: There are ranges based on benchmarking for recruitment and retention. 

3. Are there job descriptions for these staff positions?

Answer: Only have job descriptions for Administrators. Clerical (ESPA), Security (ESPA) Maintenance and Operations (TSPA) is civil service: https://www.niagaracounty.gov/employment/job_specs_for_civil_service_positions.php. Rates are also in the CBA’s that were already provided, and faculty is in the handbook which is attached as well.

communications.subject: Illinois Freedom of Information Act. Request: Flock Safety ALPR Audits 2025 (Mount Prospect Police Department)
communications.communication:
RE: Flock Safety ALPR Audits

To the FOIA Officer of Mount Prospect Police Department,

This request is made under the provisions of Illinois Freedom of Information Act. for the following records:

1. Organization Audit in Flock.
The report should include data logged from the period of June 1, 2024, to the date this request is processed. Per Flock's documentation, the Organization Audit is available within the Insights tab and is defined as searches done within the agency.

2. Network Audit in Flock.
The report should include data logged from the period of June 1, 2024, to the date this request is processed. Per Flock's documentation, the Network Audit is available within the Insights tab and is defined as searches of the organization’s Flock network by any agency in the Flock System.

Please provide the audit data in a structured format such as .csv, .xls, or another machine-readable database filetype.

3. Data Sharing
a. The names of agencies and organizations with which the Agency shares ALPR data
b. The names of agencies and organizations from which the Agency receives ALPR data
c. The names of agencies and organizations with which the Agency shares “hot list” information
d. The names of agencies and organizations from which the Agency receives “hot list” information

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the case of any applicable fees, it is requested that an estimate of the total charges be provided prior to fulfilling this request. The preferred method of receipt is through electronic delivery.

Your assistance and cooperation in this matter are greatly appreciated. A response within 5 business days, as the statute requires is anticipated.

Best,
David S. (he/him/his), Lucy Parsons Labs

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

communications.subject: California Public Records Act Request: CA CVR Data Request (2022, 2024) (San Diego County Registrar of Voters)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Cast vote record (CVR) data for the following elections:
1. 2022 Nov Midterm Election
2. 2024 Nov General Election

Specifically, for each of these elections, I’m looking for the full anonymized record of votes cast generated by the relevant voting system technology in San Diego County in that year. Alameda County has an example of these records posted for the 2024 General Election on their Election Information for November 2024 under the name “Cast Vote Records (CVR) Report”. 

Please let me know if you need any further clarification on the type of data that I am requesting.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Aleksandra Conevska

The County is reviewing your request and seeking responsive records. Pursuant to Government Code Section 7922.535, the County is extending the time for its determination. We will provide a determination on your request on or before June 5, 2025. Nothing in this letter should be construed as a representation that the County has all of the records requested or that such records, if they exist, are subject to public disclosure. Please note that 72 hours after your request is concluded, your request and any released records will become publicly available. communications.subject: Oregon Public Records Law Request: Jessica Krug criminal records request
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Oregon Public Records Law, I hereby request the following records:

Under the Oregon Public Records Law, §192.410 et seq., I am requesting an opportunity to inspect or obtain copies of public records for any and all criminal and incident reports, that may include incarcerations, arrest records, convitions, violations, misdemeanors, felonies, etc. for the individual Jessica A. Krug, aka Jessica A. Kruz aka Jessica A. Cruz (DOB 04/19/1982). 

If there are any fees for searching or copying these records, please inform me if the cost will exceed $___1___.  However, I would also like to request a waiver of all fees in that the disclosure of the requested information is in the public interest and will contribute significantly to the public’s understanding of a widely known news story. I am a reporter, and this request concerns news gathering purposes. This information is not being sought for commercial purposes.
I would request a prompt response to this request.  If you expect a significant delay in responding to or in fulfilling this request, please contact me with information about when I might expect copies or the ability to inspect the requested records.
If you deny any or all of this request, please cite each specific exemption you feel justifies the refusal to release the information and notify me of the appeal procedures available to me under the law.

Thank you for considering my request.

Sincerely,

Malakai Wade

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Wondery

Wondery

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Nebraska Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

All department policy and guidance documents regarding transgender inmates, including but not limited to gender-affirming medical care, housing and treatment by staff. I also request records of any proposed and/or enacted changes to said policies made on or after Nov. 6, 2024 until date of search, if such documents exist.

I request that, if appropriate, fees be waived as I believe this request is in the public interest. The requested documents will be made available to the general public free of charge as part of the public information service at MuckRock.com, processed by a representative of the news media/press and is made in the process of news gathering and not for commercial usage.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 4 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Ileana Garnand

title: Data Request for Local Ballot Initiatives/Referenda (Secretary of State)

communications.subject: Nevada Public Records Act Request: Data Request for Local Ballot Initiatives/Referenda (Secretary of State)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Nevada Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

I am requesting data on local ballot initiatives/referenda that took place in the state since 1972. Specifically, I need the following information to be included in the data.

1. Text of the ballot initiative/referendum
2. Local government where the election took place.
3. County where the local government is located
4. Election date
5. Result of election (votes for, votes against, pass/fail)
6. Threshold to pass (50%, two-thirds, etc)

This website from California provides a good example of the type of data I am requesting:
https://data.ca.gov/dataset/election-data/resource/67e83a65-2b55-41ec-9420-b33b666d4711

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Jimin Han

title: Clinton Sanitation Use of Laurens County Transfer Station

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the South Carolina Public Records Law, I hereby request the following records:

1. Any and all agreements, memorandums of understanding (MOUs), authorizations, or written permissions between the City of Clinton and Laurens County (or any of its departments) that authorize Clinton Sanitation to dispose of waste at the Laurens County Transfer Station (formerly the old Laurens landfill).

2. Weigh tickets, intake logs, daily reports, manifests, billing statements, or invoices documenting any waste received from the City of Clinton or its sanitation department, including waste routed to Twin Chimney landfill.

3. Internal emails, letters, or communications between Laurens County staff or officials and the City of Clinton (or its sanitation department) regarding trash disposal, dump site access, or waste transport arrangements.

4. Any records or documentation maintained by Laurens County Recycling and Collections Department that reference the City of Clinton’s use of county-operated waste facilities or routes used to deliver municipal waste.

This request follows a prior FOIA submission that was denied based on the claim that no responsive records exist. However, recent public statements from a sanitation worker have confirmed daily waste disposal operations by Clinton at the Laurens County Transfer Station, which is operated by the Laurens County Recycling and Collections Department. This indicates responsive documents do, in fact, exist.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 15 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Edwin Chadwick

Please mail or deliver your appeal to: 
The Office of Police Accountability

Seattle, WA 98124-4986 
 
If you have any questions, you may send a message using the Police Records Request Center or call the Public Disclosure Desk at 206-684-5481.

Angela Dewitt 
Seattle Police Department 
Legal Unit

patience.

title: Reports and studies related to Amtrak service to Montreal

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Reports and studies related to Amtrak service to Montreal
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

A copy of any report or study that was completed between January 2022 and May 22, 2025 related to efforts to extend the Amtrak Vermonter service to Montreal and/or establish a rail passenger preclearance/clearance facility at Montreal Central Station.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Ben Heckscher

communications.subject: Texas Public Information Act Request: Texas DOC transgender policies
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Texas Public Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

All department policy and guidance documents regarding transgender inmates, including but not limited to gender-affirming medical care, housing and treatment by staff. I also request records of any proposed and/or enacted changes to said policies made on or after Nov. 6, 2024 until date of search, if such documents exist.

I request that, if appropriate, fees be waived as I believe this request is in the public interest. The requested documents will be made available to the general public free of charge as part of the public information service at MuckRock.com, processed by a representative of the news media/press and is made in the process of news gathering and not for commercial usage.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Ileana Garnand

communications.subject: RE: Texas Public Information Act Request: Texas DOC transgender policies
communications.communication:
Your request was received and sent for processing.

Please understand that your response or records WILL NOT come from the PIA email, but will come from the department who processed your request and their email will end with:  tdcj.texas.gov

The Texas Department of Criminal Justice (TDCJ) is allowed 10 business days (Monday through Friday, excluding holidays) to process requests.

All requests are processed in the order in which they are received.

Priority cannot be given based on need or urgency.

Your patience is appreciated.

Respectfully,
Texas Department of Criminal Justice - PIA
Open Records Coordinator
Office of General Counsel

Please be sure to check your “Junk” and “Spam” folders as your records could be placed in one of those folders depending on your email settings.

communications.subject: Georgia Open Records Act Request: GA CVR Collection (2020, 2022) (Ware County Board Of Elections & Registration)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Georgia Open Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Cast vote record (CVR) data for the following elections:
1. 2020 Nov General Election
2. 2022 Nov Midterm Election

Specifically, I’m looking for the full anonymized record of votes cast each election generated by the Dominion voting system. Forsyth County has an example of these records posted for the 2024 General Election under the name “Cast Vote Records (CVR) Report” at this link: https://www.forsythco.com/Departments-Offices/Voter-Registrations-Elections/Election-Results. Please let me know if you need any further clarification on the type of data that I am requesting.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 3 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Aleksandra Conevska
